  "prompt": "How do I find an engine for an SAE Supra?",
  "response": "Finding an engine for an SAE (Society of Automotive Engineers) Supra typically involves a few steps, especially if you're looking for a specific type of engine for a project. Here\u2019s a guide to help you:\n\n1. **Determine Your Requirements**: \n   - Identify whether you're looking for a complete engine, a used engine, or specific components.\n   - Consider the engine specifications you need, such as power output, displacement, fuel type, and compliance with SAE regulations.\n\n2. **Visit Online Marketplaces**:\n   - Websites like eBay, Craigslist, and Facebook Marketplace often have listings for used engines.\n   - Specialty automotive forums or websites focused on Toyota or Supra communities can be excellent resources for leads.\n\n3. **Check Auto Parts Stores**:\n   - Local auto parts stores or chains might have access to engine suppliers or can help you locate an engine.\n   - Some specialty performance shops may offer rebuilt engines or performance upgrades for the Supra.\n\n4. **Consult with Salvage Yards**:\n   - Contact local salvage yards or auto recyclers that specialize in imports or performance vehicles to see if they have a Toyota Supra engine available.\n  \n5. **Contact Engine Rebuilders**:\n   - Reach out to companies that specialize in rebuilding engines or customizing them. They may have what you need or can direct you to someone who does.\n\n6. **Toyota Dealership**:\n   - If you are looking for a new engine or OEM parts, contacting a Toyota dealership is a good option, though it may be more expensive.\n\n7. **Networking**: \n   - Engage with the car enthusiast community. Online forums, social media groups, and local car meetups can connect you with individuals who may have leads on where to find an engine.\n\n8. **Specialty Engine Suppliers**:\n   - Some companies specialize in performance and racing engines and may have options specifically designed for competition use, like those involved in SAE competitions.\n\n9. **Consider Engine Swaps**:\n   - If you\u2019re open to it, consider other Toyota engines that could be swapped into your Supra, as there are many options available that could meet your performance needs.\n\nMake sure to verify the condition of the engine and any warranties or return policies before making a purchase to ensure it's suitable for your needs.",
